hwType.name: hwType
hwType.description: An identifier for the Annex hardware type.

hwRev.name: hwRev
hwRev.description: The revision level of the hardware platform.

romRev.name: romRev
romRev.description: The revision number of the ROM Monitor software.

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The serial number assigned to the unit.

memorySize.name: memorySize
memorySize.description: The amount of memory present in the unit.

swType.name: swType
swType.description: The software version currently running on the Annex.

swBuild.name: swBuild
swBuild.description: The full name of the software build, including the software version, major and minor version numbers and the date and time of the build.

imageName.name: imageName
imageName.description: The name of the most recently booted image.

bootHost.name: bootHost
bootHost.description: The Internet address of the host from which the Annex booted.

defaultDomain.name: defaultDomain
defaultDomain.description: The default domain name provided by the DNS nameserver.

currentDate.name: currentDate
currentDate.description: The current date and time provided by the time server.

usableMemory.name: usableMemory
usableMemory.description: The amount of available for data buffers and other structures after the Annex has booted.

freeMemory.name: freeMemory
freeMemory.description: The amount of currently available memory.

minFreeMemory.name: minFreeMemory
minFreeMemory.description: The minimum amount of free memory since booting the Annex.

cpuUtilization.name: cpuUtilization
cpuUtilization.description: Percent of CPU time currently being used.

maxProcs.name: maxProcs
maxProcs.description: The total number of process structures allocated for use.

mostProcs.name: mostProcs
mostProcs.description: The maximum number of active processes since the Annex was booted.

activeProcs.name: activeProcs
activeProcs.description: The number of currently active processes.

cpuIRescheds.name: cpuIRescheds
cpuIRescheds.description: The number of processes whose time slice has expired in the last minute.

cpuTRescheds.name: cpuTRescheds
cpuTRescheds.description: The total number of processes whose time slice has expired since booting the Annex.

contextISwtchs.name: contextISwtchs
contextISwtchs.description: The number of context switches in the last minute.

contextTSwtchs.name: contextTSwtchs
contextTSwtchs.description: The total number of context switches since booting the Annex.

cpuIActivates.name: cpuIActivates
cpuIActivates.description: The number of processes that were activated in the last minute.

cpuTActivates.name: cpuTActivates
cpuTActivates.description: The number of processes that were activated since booting the Annex.

maxCallouts.name: maxCallouts
maxCallouts.description: The number of allocated Callout structures for timed events in the Annex.

leastCallouts.name: leastCallouts
leastCallouts.description: The minimum number of Callout structures available since last booting the Annex.

freeCallouts.name: freeCallouts
freeCallouts.description: The current number of free Callout structures.

totalPorts.name: totalPorts
totalPorts.description: The number of serial ports on this Annex.

totalInChars.name: totalInChars
totalInChars.description: The total number of characters received on all serial ports.

totalOutChars.name: totalOutChars
totalOutChars.description: The total number of characters transmitted on all serial ports.

totalParityErrs.name: totalParityErrs
totalParityErrs.description: The total number of parity errors detected on all serial ports.

totalOverrunErrs.name: totalOverrunErrs
totalOverrunErrs.description: The total number of overruns detected on all serial ports.

totalFramingErrs.name: totalFramingErrs
totalFramingErrs.description: The total number of framing errors detected on all serial ports.

anxpPortIndex.name: anxpPortIndex
anxpPortIndex.description: A unique number from 1 to totalPorts that identifies each serial port.

anxpMode.name: anxpMode
anxpMode.description: This parameter defines the mode for access to the serial line port. The default is cli

anxpCtrlLines.name: anxpCtrlLines
anxpCtrlLines.description: The type of hardware control used on the port: modem control (dcddtr), flow control (ctsrts), or both.

anxpBidirModem.name: anxpBidirModem
anxpBidirModem.description: This parameter controls whether the port is configured for adaptive use with a bidirectional modem.

anxpAllowBcast.name: anxpAllowBcast
anxpAllowBcast.description: Controls whether the serial port can receive administrative broadcast messages.

anxpBcastDirection.name: anxpBcastDirection
anxpBcastDirection.description: Defines the direction that an administrative broadcast message is sent. This parameter is valid only when the port is defined as a slave port by the anxpMode parameter.

anxpInputStartChar.name: anxpInputStartChar
anxpInputStartChar.description: The control character sequence that restarts input if the charPortInFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff.

anxpInputStopChar.name: anxpInputStopChar
anxpInputStopChar.description: The control character sequence that stops input if the charPortInFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff.

anxpOutputStartChar.name: anxpOutputStartChar
anxpOutputStartChar.description: The control character sequence that restarts output if the charPortOutFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff.

anxpOutputStopChar.name: anxpOutputStopChar
anxpOutputStopChar.description: The control character sequence that stops output if the charPortOutFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff.

anxpIxanyFlowCtl.name: anxpIxanyFlowCtl
anxpIxanyFlowCtl.description: This parameter specifies whether any input character will be treated as a start (xon) character when output has been suspended by a stop (xoff) character.

anxpLongBreak.name: anxpLongBreak
anxpLongBreak.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex returns the user to the CLI prompt after receiving a break greater than two seconds.

anxpShortBreak.name: anxpShortBreak
anxpShortBreak.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex returns the user to the CLI prompt after receiving a break shorter than two seconds.

anxpForwardTimer.name: anxpForwardTimer
anxpForwardTimer.description: This parameter defines the inter-character timer that sets the amount of time, in tens of milliseconds, that will elapse before forwarding the received data. The value of zero turns off the timer.

anxpForwardCount.name: anxpForwardCount
anxpForwardCount.description: Specifies the number of received characters buffered for the port by the Annex before forwarding the characters to the host or network.

anxpImask7Bits.name: anxpImask7Bits
anxpImask7Bits.description: When enabled, instructs the Annex to ignore the eighth bit of all received characters on the port.

anxpAttnChar.name: anxpAttnChar
anxpAttnChar.description: Defines a control character sequence as an attention character to return the user to the CLI prompt. The Annex-II only allows a single control character (eg. ^A), while the Annex3 and MicroAnnex allow a string of control characters to be defined (eg. ^A^B^Z).

anxpInputBufSize.name: anxpInputBufSize
anxpInputBufSize.description: The number of 256-byte blocks allocated to receive input characters from this port.

anxpInputIsActivity.name: anxpInputIsActivity
anxpInputIsActivity.description: Controls whether received input characters are considered as activity for the port.

anxpOutputIsActivity.name: anxpOutputIsActivity
anxpOutputIsActivity.description: Controls whether transmitted output characters are considered as activity for the port.

anxpInactivityTimer.name: anxpInactivityTimer
anxpInactivityTimer.description: The amount of time, in minutes, which a port can remain inactive before the Annex terminates all sessions and resets the port. A value of 0 disables the timer.

anxpResetIdleTimer.name: anxpResetIdleTimer
anxpResetIdleTimer.description: Defines whether input or output resets the idle timer for the port.

anxpCliInactivity.name: anxpCliInactivity
anxpCliInactivity.description: The amount of time, in minutes, that the Annex waits before hanging up the serial port after it becomes idle. A value of 0 turns off the timer. A value of 255 means immediate, which causes the Annex to hang up the port immediately after exiting from the last job.

anxpCliSecurity.name: anxpCliSecurity
anxpCliSecurity.description: This parameter controls whether security is enabled for the port.

anxpConnectSecurity.name: anxpConnectSecurity
anxpConnectSecurity.description: This parameter controls whether the host-based security policy is enabled for access from the port to the network.

anxpPortServerSecurity.name: anxpPortServerSecurity
anxpPortServerSecurity.description: This parameter controls whether the host-based security policy is enabled for access to the port from the port server.

anxpPortPassword.name: anxpPortPassword
anxpPortPassword.description: This parameter defines a password for the port for local password protection.

anxpUserName.name: anxpUserName
anxpUserName.description: A string defining the user name for the user of the serial port.

anxpDedicatedAddr.name: anxpDedicatedAddr
anxpDedicatedAddr.description: When the anxpMode parameter is set to dedicated, this parameter defines the Internet address of the host to which this port can connect to.

anxpDedicatedPort.name: anxpDedicatedPort
anxpDedicatedPort.description: The application name or TCP port number to which this port can connect when the anxpMode parameter is set to dedicated. The allowed application names are 'telnet', 'rlogin', 'login', 'call', and 'mls'.

anxpPrompt.name: anxpPrompt
anxpPrompt.description: This parameter defines a port-specific prompt.

anxpTermVar.name: anxpTermVar
anxpTermVar.description: A string defining the type of terminal attached to the serial port.

anxpNewLineTerm.name: anxpNewLineTerm
anxpNewLineTerm.description: This parameter controls whether a carriage return is echoed as just a carriage return (enabled), or whether the carriage return is echoed as a carriage return and line feed.

anxpEcho.name: anxpEcho
anxpEcho.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex echoes all characters as they are received from the port.

anxpMapToLower.name: anxpMapToLower
anxpMapToLower.description: When enabled, the Annex translates all upper case characters to lower case as they are received from the port.

anxpMapToUpper.name: anxpMapToUpper
anxpMapToUpper.description: When enabled, the Annex translates all lower case characters to upper case as they are transmitted to the port.

anxpHardwareTabs.name: anxpHardwareTabs
anxpHardwareTabs.description: When enabled, this parameter allows the Annex to expand ASCII tab characters.

anxpCharErase.name: anxpCharErase
anxpCharErase.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex echoes the character erase and word erase characters for a video terminal (enabled) or for a hard-copy terminal (disabled).

anxpLineErase.name: anxpLineErase
anxpLineErase.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex echoes the line erase character for a video terminal (enabled) or for a hard-copy terminal (disabled).

anxpEraseChar.name: anxpEraseChar
anxpEraseChar.description: Defines the character erase control character sequence.

anxpEraseWord.name: anxpEraseWord
anxpEraseWord.description: Defines the word erase control character sequence.

anxpEraseLine.name: anxpEraseLine
anxpEraseLine.description: Defines the line erase control character sequence.

anxpRedisplayLine.name: anxpRedisplayLine
anxpRedisplayLine.description: Defines the reprint line control character sequence.

anxpToggleOutput.name: anxpToggleOutput
anxpToggleOutput.description: Defines the flush control character used to flush the output buffer.

anxpTelnetEscape.name: anxpTelnetEscape
anxpTelnetEscape.description: Defines the control character that returns the user to the telnet: prompt when running the CLI telnet command.

anxpNeedDsr.name: anxpNeedDsr
anxpNeedDsr.description: Specifies whether the DSR signal needs to be asserted when connecting to a slave port.

anxpTelnetCRLF.name: anxpTelnetCRLF
anxpTelnetCRLF.description: Defines what characters are transmitted out the port to the network when the End-of-Line character is sensed. 'enabled' means transmit Line-Feed and Carriage-Return. 'disabled' means transmit Carriage-Return and NULL. The default is enabled.

anxpLatbEnable.name: anxpLatbEnable
anxpLatbEnable.description: Controls interpretation of LAT Data-B packets received from host.

anxpSlipSecure.name: anxpSlipSecure
anxpSlipSecure.description: If anxEnableSecurity is not set, this parameter selects slip session logging. If anxEnableSecurity is set, this parameter permits slip access only from secure ports.

anxpNetLocalAddr.name: anxpNetLocalAddr
anxpNetLocalAddr.description: The Internet address for the Annex's side of the point-to-point (SLIP or PPP) link.

anxpNetRemoteAddr.name: anxpNetRemoteAddr
anxpNetRemoteAddr.description: The Internet address for the host at the remote end of the point-to-point (SLIP or PPP) link.

anxpSlipSubnetMask.name: anxpSlipSubnetMask
anxpSlipSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this SLIP interface.

anxpSlipLoadDumpHost.name: anxpSlipLoadDumpHost
anxpSlipLoadDumpHost.description: The Internet address of the host from which the Annex receives a load or to which the Annex sends a dump over the SLIP interface.

anxpNetMetric.name: anxpNetMetric
anxpNetMetric.description: This parameter defines the hop count to the remote end of the SLIP or PPP interface.

anxpSlipAllowDump.name: anxpSlipAllowDump
anxpSlipAllowDump.description: This parameter defines whether the Annex is allowed to dump across a SLIP link.

anxpSlipDoCompression.name: anxpSlipDoCompression
anxpSlipDoCompression.description: When enabled, the Annex will start TCP/IP header compression on this SLIP link.

anxpSlipAllowCompression.name: anxpSlipAllowCompression
anxpSlipAllowCompression.description: When enabled, the Annex will use TCP/IP header compression on this SLIP link only if the other end of the SLIP link initiates the compression.

anxpSlipMtuSize.name: anxpSlipMtuSize
anxpSlipMtuSize.description: Force the compressed SLIP interface to use a Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) of either 1024 bytes (large) or 256 bytes (small). The default is large.

anxpSlipNoIcmp.name: anxpSlipNoIcmp
anxpSlipNoIcmp.description: When enabled, the Annex will discard any ICMP packets directed to this SLIP link.

anxpSlipTos.name: anxpSlipTos
anxpSlipTos.description: When enabled, the Annex sends interactive traffic over this SLIP link before any other traffic.

anxpPppMru.name: anxpPppMru
anxpPppMru.description: This parameter defines the maximum receive unit in bytes. The default value is 1500.

anxpPppAcm.name: anxpPppAcm
anxpPppAcm.description: This parameter specifies which of the first 32 bytes (0x00, ... 0x1F) can be sent as clear text and which need to be escaped. A bit on in the mask indicates the character must be escaped. The mask should be specified as an 8 hex character string (0x1F000000 and 1F000000 are both acceptable).

anxpPppSecurityProto.name: anxpPppSecurityProto
anxpPppSecurityProto.description: Defines which security protocol will be used to authenticate the remote user. This parameter must be set and the Annex enable_security (anxEnableSecurity) must be enabled before authentication is performed. The default is none

anxpPppUserRemote.name: anxpPppUserRemote
anxpPppUserRemote.description: The username used by the Annex to identify itself if the remote PPP peer asks for authentication. Reading this parameter will return either <set> if the username is defined or <unset> if the username is not defined.

anxpPppPasswdRemote.name: anxpPppPasswdRemote
anxpPppPasswdRemote.description: The username used by the Annex to identify itself if the remote PPP peer asks for authentication. Reading this parameter will return either <set> if the password is defined or <unset> if the password is not defined.

anxpLatAuthGroupVal.name: anxpLatAuthGroupVal
anxpLatAuthGroupVal.description: This port parameter specifies which remote group codes are accessible to a user on a particular Annex port. Each port has its own set of group codes.

anxpPppDialupAddr.name: anxpPppDialupAddr
anxpPppDialupAddr.description: When enabled, the Annex requests the PPP dialup addresses from the host-based ACP.

anxpBanner.name: anxpBanner
anxpBanner.description: Specifies whether the Annex banner and message- of-the-day are displayed on the port. The default is enabled.

anxpPsHistory.name: anxpPsHistory
anxpPsHistory.description: Specifies how much data to buffer on a slave port.

anxpLocation.name: anxpLocation
anxpLocation.description: A descriptive string for a this port. This string is displayed by the CLI who command.

anxpType.name: anxpType
anxpType.description: The type of device attached to the port. The default is hardwired.

anxpCliImask7.name: anxpCliImask7
anxpCliImask7.description: Defines whether input at the CLI is masked to 7 bitx. The default is disabled.

anxpParaPorts.name: anxpParaPorts
anxpParaPorts.description: The number of parallel ports on this Annex.

anxpParaPortEntry.name: anxpParaPortEntry
anxpParaPortEntry.description: The Annex parallel port configuration parameters.

anxpParaPortIndex.name: anxpParaPortIndex
anxpParaPortIndex.description: A unique number from 1 to anxpParaPorts that identifies each parallel port.

anxpParaPortHardwareTabs.name: anxpParaPortHardwareTabs
anxpParaPortHardwareTabs.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex will send a tab character to the printer. If disabled, the tab is replaced with spaces.

anxpParaPortMapToUpper.name: anxpParaPortMapToUpper
anxpParaPortMapToUpper.description: When enabled, the Annex translates all lower case characters to upper case before transmitting the characters to the printer port.

anxpParaPortPrinterWidth.name: anxpParaPortPrinterWidth
anxpParaPortPrinterWidth.description: The defined maximum number of characters per printer line.

anxpParaPortInterface.name: anxpParaPortInterface
anxpParaPortInterface.description: The type of printer attached to the port.

anxpParaPortSpeed.name: anxpParaPortSpeed
anxpParaPortSpeed.description: The printer speed on the Micro-Annex.

anxInetAddr.name: anxInetAddr
anxInetAddr.description: The Internet address of the Annex.

anxPrefLoadAddr.name: anxPrefLoadAddr
anxPrefLoadAddr.description: The preferred load address for the Annex.

anxPrefDumpAddr.name: anxPrefDumpAddr
anxPrefDumpAddr.description: The preferred dump address for the Annex.

anxLoadDumpGateway.name: anxLoadDumpGateway
anxLoadDumpGateway.description: The Internet address of a gateway used when the preferred load or dump host is on a different network or subnet.

anxLoadDumpSeq.name: anxLoadDumpSeq
anxLoadDumpSeq.description: Lists the available network interfaces and the order that the Annex uses them when doing a down-line load or up-line dump.

anxLoadBcast.name: anxLoadBcast
anxLoadBcast.description: This parameter defines whether the Annex broadcasts for the config or the motd files if they were not found on the preferred load host.

anxServerCap.name: anxServerCap
anxServerCap.description: Defines whether the Annex can act as a file server host for another Annex. The allowable values are 'all', 'none' (the default), or one or more of the following names separated by commas: 'config', 'motd', 'image'.

anxTimeBcast.name: anxTimeBcast
anxTimeBcast.description: This parameter defines whether the Annex broadcasts for the time if the preferred load host does not provide a time server.

anxBcastAddr.name: anxBcastAddr
anxBcastAddr.description: The Internet address used by the Annex when sending broadcasts.

anxAuthAgent.name: anxAuthAgent
anxAuthAgent.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex can send an ICMP Address Mask Reply to a received ICMP Address Mask Request.

anxMaxVcli.name: anxMaxVcli
anxMaxVcli.description: The maximum number of virtual CLI connections allowed by the Annex at any one time. 0 means the Annex does not allow VCLI connections. 255 allows the Annex to maintain an unlimited number of VCLI connections.

anxIpEncapType.name: anxIpEncapType
anxIpEncapType.description: This parameter specifies whether the Annex encapsulates IP packets in the Ethernet format or the IEEE 802.2/802.3 Data Link Layer format.

anxNameServer1Type.name: anxNameServer1Type
anxNameServer1Type.description: The name service type used by the primary nameserver host.

anxNameServer1Addr.name: anxNameServer1Addr
anxNameServer1Addr.description: The Internet address of the primary nameserver host.

anxNameServer2Type.name: anxNameServer2Type
anxNameServer2Type.description: The name service type used by the secondary nameserver host.

anxNameServer2Addr.name: anxNameServer2Addr
anxNameServer2Addr.description: The Internet address of the secondary nameserver host.

anxNameServerBcast.name: anxNameServerBcast
anxNameServerBcast.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex broadcasts a name server request if the preferred name servers do not respond.

anxRwhod.name: anxRwhod
anxRwhod.description: Defines whether the Annex listens for RWHO broadcasts when building its host table.

anxMinUniqueHostNames.name: anxMinUniqueHostNames
anxMinUniqueHostNames.description: Defines whether the Annex minimum uniqueness feature is available.

anxHostTableSize.name: anxHostTableSize
anxHostTableSize.description: Defines the number of entries in the Annex host table. 0 indicates no host table. 251 sets no limit on the size of the table.

anxRouted.name: anxRouted
anxRouted.description: Defines whether the RIP-listener of the routing daemon on the Annex is enabled.

anxEnableSecurity.name: anxEnableSecurity
anxEnableSecurity.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex security system is enabled.

anxPassword.name: anxPassword
anxPassword.description: Setting this parameter changes the Annex's administration password. Reading this parameter will return either <set> if the password is defined or <unset> if the password is not defined.

anxSecurServer1Addr.name: anxSecurServer1Addr
anxSecurServer1Addr.description: The Internet address of the primary host where the Annex sends its security requests.

anxSecurServer2Addr.name: anxSecurServer2Addr
anxSecurServer2Addr.description: The Internet address of the secondary host where the Annex sends its security requests.

anxNetTurnAround.name: anxNetTurnAround
anxNetTurnAround.description: The amount of time (in seconds) that the Annex waits for a response from a security server.

anxSecurBcast.name: anxSecurBcast
anxSecurBcast.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex will broadcast its security requests when neither of the preferred security servers are available.

anxVcliSecurity.name: anxVcliSecurity
anxVcliSecurity.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex performs user validation on the virtual CLI connections.

anxVcliPassword.name: anxVcliPassword
anxVcliPassword.description: This parameter defines a password used by the Annex when setting up a virtual CLI connection.

anxAcpKey.name: anxAcpKey
anxAcpKey.description: This parameter defines the Annex's encryption key used when exchanging messages between the Annex and the security server.

anxSysLogMask.name: anxSysLogMask
anxSysLogMask.description: Defines the priority levels of events logged in the Annex syslog file. The allowable values are 'all', 'none', or one or more of the following level names separated by commas: 'emergency', 'alert', 'critical', 'error', 'warning', 'notice', 'info', 'debug'

anxSysLogFacility.name: anxSysLogFacility
anxSysLogFacility.description: This parameter defines the 4.3BSD syslog facility used in logging the Annex messages.

anxSysLogHost.name: anxSysLogHost
anxSysLogHost.description: The Internet address of the host configured to log Annex messages.

anxCliPrompt.name: anxCliPrompt
anxCliPrompt.description: The string used by the Annex to prompt all CLI users.

anxMotdFile.name: anxMotdFile
anxMotdFile.description: The host file name that contains the message-of-the-day for the Annex.

anxTftpDirName.name: anxTftpDirName
anxTftpDirName.description: Specifies the directory name to be prepended to all files (boot image, motd, macros, etc.) when booting via TFTP.

anxTftpDumpName.name: anxTftpDumpName
anxTftpDumpName.description: The full pathname of the TFTP dump file, if any.

anxTimeZone.name: anxTimeZone
anxTimeZone.description: Defines the timezone where the Annex resides in minutes west of GMT.

anxDaylightSavings.name: anxDaylightSavings
anxDaylightSavings.description: Defines the daylight savings time for the geographic location of the Annex.

anxLatKey.name: anxLatKey
anxLatKey.description: The Annex specific LAT key used to enable or disable the LAT protocol.

anxCircuitTimer.name: anxCircuitTimer
anxCircuitTimer.description: The time interval in tens of milliseconds between the transmission of LAT packets.

anxLatGroupVal.name: anxLatGroupVal
anxLatGroupVal.description: The Annex LAT group code for permitting access to LAT services. To access a specific LAT service, the Annex must have at least one enabled group code match the service's set group codes. The Annex will not maintain any information about unauthorized services. The value is displayed as a string of hex characters with each bit defining whether a specific group is enabled or disabled.

anxKeepAliveTimer.name: anxKeepAliveTimer
anxKeepAliveTimer.description: The time interval, in seconds, between the transmission of identification packets during times of network inactivity.

anxReXmitLimit.name: anxReXmitLimit
anxReXmitLimit.description: The number of times to retransmit a packet before notifying the user of a network failure.

anxServerName.name: anxServerName
anxServerName.description: A string of up to 16 characters used to name the Annex in the LAT protocol.

anxServiceLimit.name: anxServiceLimit
anxServiceLimit.description: This parameter defines the upper bound on the number of services that the Annex can maintain in its local service table.

anxConfigFile.name: anxConfigFile
anxConfigFile.description: The name of the host file that contains the alias and menu entries.

anxLatVcliGroupVal.name: anxLatVcliGroupVal
anxLatVcliGroupVal.description: This Annex parameter specifies which remote group codes are accessible to virtual cli users. All virtual cli users have the same group code. The value is displayed as a string of hex characters with each bit defining whether a specific group is enabled or disabled.

anxLatQueueMax.name: anxLatQueueMax
anxLatQueueMax.description: Defines the maximum number of host requests (HIC's) that the Annex will save in its internal queue when the requested resource is not available (port busy).

anxLatLocation.name: anxLatLocation
anxLatLocation.description: A string of up to 32 characters used to identify the location of the Annex for the LAT protocol.

anxDisabledModules.name: anxDisabledModules
anxDisabledModules.description: Defines which selectable modules are currently disabled. The allowable values are 'all', 'none' or one or more of the following names separated by commas: 'admin', 'lat', 'ppp', 'slip', 'snmp', 'nameserver', 'cli-edit'. If this is a MicroAnnex ELS, the values 'ppp' and 'slip' are not valid.

anxSysLogPort.name: anxSysLogPort
anxSysLogPort.description: Specifies the Annex port number where syslog messages are sent. If set to 0, syslog messages are not sent to an Annex port. This is independent of any host-based syslogging that may be enabled. The maximum port number allowed will depend on the highest numbered port on the specific Annex.

anxcBoot.name: anxcBoot
anxcBoot.description: The type of boot to be performed. To initiate a dump, this parameter needs to be set by the management station. The values stored in anxcBootImage, anxcBootTime, and anxcBootMsg are used as needed, depending on the boot type.

anxcBootImage.name: anxcBootImage
anxcBootImage.description: The name of the image file to be used with the boot command.

anxcBootTime.name: anxcBootTime
anxcBootTime.description: The time at which the next boot is scheduled in HH:MM format.

anxcBootMsg.name: anxcBootMsg
anxcBootMsg.description: The broadcast message to be displayed when the next boot is performed.

anxcReset.name: anxcReset
anxcReset.description: Writing a value to this object causes the annex to reset the appropriate subsystem.

anxcBcast.name: anxcBcast
anxcBcast.description: Writing a value to this object causes the annex to send the message in anxcBcastMsg to the specified port set.

anxcBcastMsg.name: anxcBcastMsg
anxcBcastMsg.description: The message to be broadcast to the Annex ports.
